 Patients were evaluated every 4 weeks and at each visit a decision on dosage changes was made based on efficacy parameters (DAS28) and occurrence of adverse events (AEs).

 Patients received MTX/placeboMTX in climbing dosages.

 Hydroxychloroquine (HCQ) was added when remission was not reached with the maximum tolerable dosage (MTD) of MTX/placeboMTX.

 If after 12 additional weeks remission was not reached, HCQ was stopped and replaced by standard of care therapy (in Group I) or placebo therapy was replaced by the corresponding verum resulting in TCZ+MTX combination therapy (in Groups II and III).

 In case remission was reached, MTX/placeboMTX and TCZ/placeboTCZ had to be decreased.

 Patients were followed for a maximum of 24 months.

